+### D2: Reopen Decisions Must Be Evaluated, Not Pre-Minted
+
+**When:** T+5
+**Context:** `claim-gate-loop` had a fixture-level reopen evaluator, but the
+wavegraph workflow did not yet carry its decisions in receipts and did not block
+pre-minted reopen artifacts.
+**Decision:** Let workflow specs provide `gateLoopState` and
+`gateLoopReopenRequests`; evaluate them inside the wavegraph slice; include the
+resulting decision receipts and invalidation metadata in the proposal-only
+slice bundle; block `gateLoopReopenDecisions` and `gateLoopStateReceipt` on
+workflow specs.
+**Rationale:** Lev DNA requires deterministic gates and immutable receipts.
+Pre-minted reopen decisions would collapse a later-gate contradiction into
+unverified worker prose.
+**Impact:** `claim-gate-wavegraph-slice.ts` and tests.
+**Code Refs:** `core/orchestration/src/proof/claim-gate-wavegraph-slice.ts`,
+`core/orchestration/src/proof/claim-gate-wavegraph-slice.test.ts`
