+### D6: Injected Provider Runner Seam Before Transport Adapters
+
+**When:** T+9
+**Context:** The overgoal requires "all the models laid out": lots of Claude
+Bridge controller lanes, top Chinese-family OpenRouter checks, xAI/Grok,
+Google Gemini TUI, and Codex/local. The existing Gate 0A model-lane compiler
+required those lanes, but did not yet provide a runner contract that provider
+transport adapters could emit into.
+**Decision:** Add `runClaimGateModelLaneRuntimeRunners`, an injected provider
+runner seam that executes lane manifests through provider-keyed runners and
+normalizes results into `ClaimGateModelLaneRuntimeOutcome` before Gate 0A
+aggregation. The seam handles success, timeout, schema-invalid output,
+provider error, blocked lanes, and unavailable lanes as advisory-only receipted
+outcomes.
+**Rationale:** This makes model diversity structural without hardcoding
+network calls into the deterministic proof core. Real Claude/OpenRouter/xAI/
+Google/Codex transports can plug in later, but they must preserve receipts and
+failure packets through the same gate path.
+**Impact:** `claim-gate-wavegraph-slice.ts`, tests, public exports, plan,
+goal, alignment report, implementation report, packet refresh.
+**Code Refs:** `core/orchestration/src/proof/claim-gate-wavegraph-slice.ts`,
+`core/orchestration/src/proof/claim-gate-wavegraph-slice.test.ts`
+**Canonical Ref:** `.lev/pm/plans/plan-claimgate-gate-ratchet-wavegraph.md`
