+### Gate 2: Actual Loader
+
+The runtime actually loads the member's skills/MMMs/sources and records hashes in the worker receipt.
+
+### Gate 3: Gate Loop Kernel
+
+Implement reusable verify/reject/requeue loop semantics with FailurePackets, graveyard, requeue queue, budgets, and circuit breaker.
+
+### Gate 4: Axiom -> Constraint -> Gate Digger
+
+Mine source/work/result material into proposal-only axioms, constraints, gates, and attractor-basin deltas.
+
+### Gate 5: Nested Wave/Council Compiler
+
+Compile waves as phases containing councils; councils can contain subcouncils/durable teams/agents; waves and councils can loop.
+
+### Gate 6: Management Plane Sidecars
+
+Add resource, laggard, context, reroute, receipt, and escalation management as parallel sidecars.
+
+### Gate 7: Repair / Requeue / Reroute Semantics
+
+Failures route to the right lane: same member, alternate skill, alternate model, different council, human escalation, or graveyard.
+
+### Gate 8: Source / Skill Integration Packs
+
+Formalize OxRicker, oh-my-openagent/ohmycodex, Wizard, autoresearch, premortem, Ponytail, Krypton, and Lev agent skills as packs with claim ceilings.
+
+### Gate 9: Lev Graph Patch Admission
+
+Council/gate outputs become proposal-only graph patches consumed by host Lev. ClaimGate is a projection/admission lane, not canon.
+
+### Gate 10: Sendable Patch Packet For JP
+
+Package the work as a clean patch, docs, receipts, and honest claim ceiling that JP can review without swallowing a giant rewrite.
+
+## First Slice
+
+The first slice should prove the runtime floor without losing the broader object:
