+
+## Runtime Topology
+
+### Work Plane
+
+```text
+WizardRun
+  WaveSequence
+    Wave
+      Council
+        SubCouncil | DurableTeam | Agent
+          SkillRefs + MMMRefs + SourceRefs + ToolRefs
+```
+
+Waves are not the same as councils. A wave is a phase of work. A wave contains one or more councils. Councils can contain subcouncils, durable teams, or agents. Waves may run sequentially, parallelize internally, loop back on themselves, or cause the whole wave sequence to loop back to an earlier wave.
+
+### Management Plane
+
+Management runs alongside work; it does not become another work council hidden in the main topology.
+
+- Conductor: advances waves, pauses, resumes, and records state.
+- Resource Manager: model/provider/budget/concurrency allocation.
+- Context Loader: loads skills, MMMs, source packs, object cards, and graph facts.
+- Laggard Monitor: detects slow/stalled/low-quality branches.
+- Reroute Manager: maps failures to repair lanes and alternate models/skills.
+- Receipt Manager: seals evidence, hashes loaded context, and writes receipts.
+- Claim Ceiling Watcher: blocks overclaims and host-authority self-assertion.
+
+### Gate Plane
+
+Gate Plane validates every transition:
+
+- Lev gates from `.lev/validation-gates.yaml`.
+- ClaimGate object/evidence/scope/falsifier/manifest/signature gates.
+- Wave/council/member manifest gates.
+- Multi-model lane formation and provenance gates.
+- Source-pack read and consumption gates.
+- Host steering admission gates.
+- Circuit breaker gates after repeated failure.
