+### Gate 1: Cognitive Member Manifest Gate
+
+Purpose: prevent random swarms. Every worker, council member, subcouncil, or management sidecar must declare what mind it is allowed to be.
+
+Manifest contract:
+
+```ts
+interface CognitiveMemberManifest {
+  memberId: string;
+  kind: 'agent' | 'council' | 'subcouncil' | 'durable_team' | 'management_sidecar';
+  role: string;
+  mmmRefs: string[];
+  skillRefs: string[];
+  sourceRefs: string[];
+  toolRefs: string[];
+  inputContract: Record<string, unknown>;
+  outputContract: Record<string, unknown>;
+  gateContracts: string[];
+  requeuePolicy: {
+    onFailure: 'repair_same_member' | 'reroute_skill' | 'reroute_model' | 'escalate_human' | 'graveyard';
+    maxAttempts: number;
+  };
+  receiptTarget: string;
+}
+```
+
+Internal loop:
+
+1. Compile member manifests.
+2. Validate refs are resolvable.
+3. Reject members without role, skills, MMMs, source refs, output schema, gates, and requeue policy.
+4. Produce a failure packet per invalid member.
+5. Requeue manifest repair until clean or blocked.
