+# ClaimGate Overgoal Alignment Audit - 2026-06-23
+
+## Scope
+
+Audited:
+
+- `.lev/pm/plans/goal-claimgate-overgoal-20260623.md`
+- `.lev/pm/plans/plan-claimgate-gate-ratchet-wavegraph.md`
+- `docs/design/design-codex-ratchet-claim-gate-bridge.md`
+
+Against:
+
+- `dna/graph.yaml`
+- `dna/entities.yaml`
+- `dna/vernacular.yaml`
+- `dna/gates.yaml`
+- `.lev/validation-gates.yaml`
+
+Claim ceiling: `alignment_audit_and_goal_doc_tightening_not_runtime_proof`.
+
+## Verdict
+
+Status: `warn_corrected`
+
+The saved goal did not fully go off track. It correctly preserved the core
+object: a Lev-native cognitive wavegraph patch with skill/MMM/source-loaded
+members, nested waves/councils, management sidecars, OxRicker-style gate loops,
+Codex Ratchet axiom/constraint/gate digging, and proposal-only host Lev
+admission.
+
+It was still too easy to misread as a strong conceptual manifesto instead of a
+Lev executable patch. The goal file has now been tightened to require a
+FlowMind / execution-contract shaped workflow spec, tiny fixture, deterministic
+validator, and receipt trail as the first tangible surface.
+
+## Alignment Findings
+
+### Pass: Not Random Swarm Work
+
+The goal requires every agent, council member, durable team, subcouncil, and
+management sidecar to carry a cognitive member manifest with role, authority,
+MMM refs, skills, sources, contracts, gate contract, requeue policy, and receipt
+target.
+
+This matches the user constraint: agents must be structured members with loaded
+skills/MMMs, not ad hoc workers.
+
+### Pass: Waves Are Distinct From Councils
+
+The goal now preserves the needed distinction:
+
+- A wave is a phase of work.
+- A council is a structured group inside a wave.
+- Councils can contain subcouncils, durable teams, agents, model lanes, skill
+  lanes, and source lanes.
+- Waves can loop internally and the wave sequence can loop back.
+
+This matches the Wizard/wave lineage without flattening waves into councils.
+
+### Pass: Management Plane Is Parallel
+
+The goal keeps management sidecars outside the work plane. They route context,
+laggards, budget, model health, failures, duplicate work, stalled branches,
+receipts, requeue targets, and kill switches.
+
+They may route, throttle, quarantine, or request repair. They may not silently
+mutate results or promote work.
+
+### Pass: Gate Loops Are Internal Loops
+
