+### Nested Wave Fixture
+
+The fixture is intentionally small but structurally load-bearing:
+
+- two waves
+- councils inside waves
+- management sidecars separate from councils
+- receipt-bearing management actions for context loading and failure reroute
+- one claim fails `evidence_manifest`
+- one `FailurePacket`
+- one requeue
+- deterministic ClaimGate loop accepts only after repaired evidence
+
+### Gate 6: Management Plane Sidecar Receipts
+
+The slice now requires management sidecars to emit receipt-bearing management
+actions. A management action must:
+
+- reference a real management sidecar in the same wave
+- declare a bounded purpose such as `context_load` or `reroute_failure`
+- carry input/output refs
+- carry a receipt ref
+- keep `authority: route_or_quarantine_only`
+- keep `claimCeiling: management_sidecar_not_promotion`
+
+The runtime emits a `managementPlaneReceipt` and includes that receipt in the
+proposal-only slice bundle. Management can route or quarantine; it cannot
+promote, rewrite, or suppress work-plane receipts.
